UID:jkGqJ8nACJ7A-7KnMXPP1
SUMMARY:Buying and Selling Businesses
DTSTAMP:20260701T101451Z
DTSTART:20260708T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Lenny Saizan\, owner of Murphy Business & Financial – Sout
	hwest Houston\, Managing Director of Urban Capital Network\, and creator o
	f the Legacy Maximizer exit strategy\, for a practical\, real-world discus
	sion on selling and buying businesses. \nSelling or acquiring a business i
	s one of the most significant financial decisions most entrepreneurs will 
	ever make\, yet many owners and buyers go through the process for the firs
	t time without a clear roadmap. This session breaks down the transaction p
	rocess from both sides of the table and highlights how thoughtful planning
	\, proper valuation\, and coordinated advice can materially impact outcome
	s. \nFor business owners\, the discussion centers on how to maximize enter
	prise value\, prepare for a future exit\, and align business decisions wit
	h personal wealth\, tax\, and legacy goals. For buyers\, the session explo
	res entrepreneurship through acquisition\, including how buying an existin
	g business can reduce risk\, generate immediate cash flow\, and serve as a
	 growth strategy for current operators. \nDrawing on his experience as a b
	usiness broker\, investment advisor\, and financial professional\, Lenny c
	onnects the technical aspects of M&A with broader exit planning and wealth
	 strategy considerations\, helping attendees understand not just how trans
	actions work\, but how they fit into a bigger financial picture. \nTopics 
	include: \n\nCurrent market conditions and buyer demand\nWhen to prepare t
	o sell or buy\nKey drivers of business value\nHow businesses are valued in
	 the real world\nRecasting and normalizing financial statements\nOverview 
	of the sales and acquisition process\nThe role of advisors and the deal te
	am\nTax\, insurance\, and planning considerations before and after a trans
	action\n\nThis session is ideal for business owners considering a sale now
	 or in the future\, prospective buyers exploring acquisition\, and profess
	ionals who support small business owners through growth and transition. \n
	Presenter\n \nLenny Saizan is the owner and lead broker of Murphy Business
	 & Financial – Southwest Houston\, where he advises business owners on exi
	t planning\, value maximization\, and business sales\, and supports buyers
	 pursuing acquisitions and franchises. He is also the co-founder and Manag
	ing Director of Urban Capital Network\, an investment firm focused on expa
	nding access to private investment opportunities. \nEarlier in his career\
	, Lenny spent two decades in engineering\, automation\, and oil and gas\, 
	leading teams across operational controls\, financial controls\, and audit
	. He holds a Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering from Louisiana 
	State University and an MBA from Tulane University. His credentials includ
	e Certified Mergers & Acquisition Professional\, Six Sigma Green Belt\, an
	d Project Management Professional. In 2025\, he was recognized as Deal Mak
	er of The Year at Houston Dealmakers conference. \n \n\nhttps://iondistric
	t.com/event/buying-and-selling-businesses-8/\n\nFrom Ion District
URL:https://iondistrict.com/event/buying-and-selling-businesses-8/
LOCATION:Ion – Conference Room 029 – 030\, 4201 Main St\, Houston\, TX\, 77
	002\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:ion-district
CATEGORIES:Ion District
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
